From 45e30654dfcc248365d18cad66d2bd83fc853811 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 12:13:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] fix: eliminate cache race condition and config re-read on
 every getter

- cache.py: guard read-modify-write cycles with a cross-process lock file
  and write JSON atomically (temp file + os.replace), so concurrent runs
  (e.g. two cron jobs) can no longer lose writes or corrupt the cache
- config.py: parse config.json once and cache it in memory, invalidating
  by (mtime, size), instead of re-reading the file on every getter call

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
